  <prompt>
    Refine `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/services/communicationApi.ts` to land the client-side half of the FR-21 DTO rename + the uniform error contract:
    (a) Add `attachmentDriveItemIds?: string[]` as the canonical attachment field on the request type.
    (b) Mark `attachmentDocumentIds?: string[]` as `@deprecated` (logs `console.warn` once per session when used).
    (c) Add a new exported class `SendCommunicationError extends Error` exposing `status`, `code`, `detail`, `correlationId` parsed from the BFF's ProblemDetails (ADR-019) error response.
    (d) `sendCommunication()` MUST throw `SendCommunicationError` on any non-2xx response.
    (e) Update docstrings on the request type and `sendCommunication()` to clarify the Microsoft Graph `driveItem` ID semantics (NOT `sprk_document` GUIDs).

    Empirical finding (CLAUDE.md row 2): the file already has `sendCommunication()` but is missing both the `SendCommunicationError` export and the `attachmentDriveItemIds` field. This task is additive — no breaking change to existing callers.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke shared-library engineer. Authoritative on `@spaarke/ui-components` `services/` layer. Familiar with the existing `communicationApi.ts` pattern (auth decoupling via injected `authenticatedFetch`, per NFR-02). Familiar with ADR-019 (ProblemDetails) and ADR-028 (auth v2 boundary — `@spaarke/auth` MUST NOT be imported in shared lib).
  </role>

  <goal>
    `communicationApi.ts` exports a `SendCommunicationError` class and accepts BOTH `attachmentDriveItemIds` (canonical) and `attachmentDocumentIds` (deprecated). When the deprecated field is used, a console warning fires once per session (not per call). When a send fails with non-2xx, `sendCommunication()` throws `SendCommunicationError` with `status`/`code`/`detail`/`correlationId` parsed from the BFF ProblemDetails. Existing callers (5 wizard email steps + `SummarizeFilesDialog` + `FilePreviewDialog` + `DocumentEmailWizard` + `EntityCreationService.sendEmail`) continue to work unmodified. `npm run build` + `npm run lint` clean in `@spaarke/ui-components`.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      `communicationApi.ts` is the single typed gateway between every Spaarke client surface and the BFF `/api/communications/send` endpoint. R3's goal of "exactly one client function handles every email send" (success criterion #1) hinges on this file. Every Wave 1+ component uses it. The error class lands here because NFR-06 mandates a uniform error contract replacing the 3 inconsistent patterns identified in the driver assessment (throw `Error` / return `{success, warning}` / push to `warnings[]`).

      Per NFR-02 + ADR-028, shared library components MUST NOT import `@spaarke/auth` directly. `authenticatedFetch` is injected as a prop / parameter. This task preserves that boundary — do NOT add an `@spaarke/auth` import to `communicationApi.ts`.

      Per ADR-019, BFF errors come back as ProblemDetails: a JSON body with `type`, `title`, `status`, `detail`, `traceId` (or `instance`) + optional `correlationId`. `SendCommunicationError` parses that shape; if the body is non-JSON or non-ProblemDetails, fall back to a minimal error with `status` only.

      Per the task brief: deprecation warning MUST fire ONCE per session (not every call) to avoid console spam. Use a module-level `let deprecationWarned = false` flag.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/services/communicationApi.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/services/__tests__/</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="project">FR-20 + FR-09 are the binding requirements for this task.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">NFR-05: non-breaking — existing callers using `attachmentDocumentIds` MUST continue to send mail successfully.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">NFR-06: uniform error contract — `SendCommunicationError` replaces 3 existing inconsistent patterns across the codebase.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">Parse ProblemDetails shape: `{ type, title, status, detail, traceId|instance, correlationId? }`. Fall back gracefully on non-JSON responses.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">`@spaarke/auth` MUST NOT be imported in this file. `authenticatedFetch` is injected via parameter (existing pattern at `communicationApi.ts:21-23`).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">No styling impact in this task; listed for completeness per task brief.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Deprecation warning fires ONCE per session (module-level flag), not per call.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">XML/TSDoc docstrings updated to explicitly say "Microsoft Graph driveItem IDs (NOT `sprk_document` GUIDs)."</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-033">The new ADR (task 001) codifies the canonical pattern. Confirm this task aligns.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/spec.md</file>
