    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Auth decoupling (injected fetch)" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/services/communicationApi.ts">
        Existing pattern at line 21-23 (per spec). `authenticatedFetch` is a function parameter; the file does NOT import `@spaarke/auth`. Preserve this.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="ProblemDetails parsing" location=".claude/adr/ADR-019-problemdetails-error-responses.md">
        Server returns `{ type, title, status, detail, instance | traceId, correlationId? }`. Client parses with a try/catch around `await response.json()`; falls back to a minimal error on non-JSON.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="One-shot deprecation warning" location="any standard JS module">
        Module-level `let deprecationWarned = false;` flag. First call sets it to true after `console.warn(...)`. Subsequent calls skip the warn.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/services/communicationApi.ts` end-to-end. Identify: (a) the request type definition, (b) `sendCommunication()` function shape, (c) current error handling (per empirical finding, it's a thrown `Error` — confirm).</step>
    <step order="2">Author `SendCommunicationError` class in the same file: `export class SendCommunicationError extends Error { readonly status: number; readonly code?: string; readonly detail?: string; readonly correlationId?: string; constructor(...) { super(message); this.name = 'SendCommunicationError'; ... } }`. Include a static `async fromResponse(response: Response): Promise&lt;SendCommunicationError&gt;` that does the ProblemDetails parse with a fallback.</step>
    <step order="3">Edit the request type to add `attachmentDriveItemIds?: string[]` with a TSDoc clarifying "Microsoft Graph driveItem IDs (NOT `sprk_document` GUIDs). Canonical field per ADR-033." Edit `attachmentDocumentIds?: string[]` with `@deprecated Use attachmentDriveItemIds. Removed in R4 (FR-21).` TSDoc.</step>
    <step order="4">Add module-level `let _deprecationWarned = false;` flag. In `sendCommunication()`, after parameter destructure, add: if `request.attachmentDocumentIds !== undefined && !_deprecationWarned` → `console.warn('[Spaarke] attachmentDocumentIds is deprecated. Use attachmentDriveItemIds (FR-21).')` + `_deprecationWarned = true`.</step>
    <step order="5">In `sendCommunication()` body: after `authenticatedFetch(...)` call, if `!response.ok` → `throw await SendCommunicationError.fromResponse(response);`. Confirm this replaces any prior `throw new Error(...)` on non-2xx.</step>
    <step order="6">Confirm the request payload sent to BFF includes BOTH `attachmentDriveItemIds` AND `attachmentDocumentIds` when callers populate them (task 002's BFF mapping handles precedence). Do NOT drop or rename either field client-side.</step>
    <step order="7">Update docstrings on `sendCommunication()` to explicitly call out: (a) the driveItem semantics, (b) the throw of `SendCommunicationError`, (c) the deprecation note for `attachmentDocumentIds`.</step>
    <step order="8">Run `npm run build` in `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/` — confirm clean.</step>
    <step order="9">Run `npm run lint` in `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/` — confirm clean.</step>
    <step order="9.1">Quick search for downstream callers using `Grep` on `communicationApi` / `sendCommunication` in `src/`. Skim each call site to confirm: (a) callers do NOT `instanceof Error` on the throw (would break with `SendCommunicationError extends Error`, but the new subclass should pass that check), (b) no caller relies on a specific error MESSAGE shape (the new message is informative but not contractual). Record findings in task notes.</step>
    <step order="9.5">FULL-rigor quality gates: invoke `code-review` skill on the diff; invoke `adr-check` skill against `spec.md`. Address any Critical findings.</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 005 ✅ completed; confirm task 011 + task 022 dependencies satisfied.</step>
    <step order="11">Update `current-task.md` per task-execute protocol: status → completed; advance to next pending task.</step>
  </steps>

