  <notes>
    Task 008 covers the Jest unit tests for `SendCommunicationError` behavior + deprecation warning. This task implements; task 008 verifies.

    The `code` field on `SendCommunicationError` is intended for ProblemDetails extensions (e.g., `code: "ATTACHMENT_TOO_LARGE"`). If the BFF doesn't currently populate it, leave the field nullable; the Wave 1 engine validation contract (FR-08) consumes the canonical codes locally and the server side rounds them out over time.

    Per task brief, ADR-021 is listed for completeness only — there is no styling change in this task.

    `attachmentDriveItemIds` carries Graph `driveItem` IDs. These come from `wizardContext.uploadedFiles[].driveItemId` (per Wave 5 task 075 + spec A5). DocumentEmailWizard line 494's bug is that it shipped `sprk_document` GUIDs into the deprecated field; that's fixed in Wave 5.

    Per CLAUDE.md §10 (BFF hygiene): client-side change. No BFF publish-size impact for this task.
  </notes>

